The first step has been taken.
I have exited Facebook, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deactivated my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website — Google Analytics — and felt great about it.
To better support GDPR compliance, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business over in the coming weeks.
I transferred the MX records to Proton, and now I have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email verification anymore.
